WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.981
Look at this desk for a second. Pencil. Water. Spoon. Salt. A copper coin. Even the air you just breathed out.

00:08.501 --> 00:13.931
They could not look more different. One writes, one flows, one clinks.

00:14.411 --> 00:21.100
And the salt? Stir it into water and it seems to vanish, but it is still in there, hiding in plain sight.

00:21.780 --> 00:25.356
Chemistry starts with one brilliant, slightly cheeky idea:

00:25.596 --> 00:27.639
none of this is magic.

00:28.139 --> 00:33.724
It is all built. Built from pieces so small your eyes will never win that argument.

00:34.574 --> 00:43.278
Water, metal, air, sugar, the graphite in your pencil - once you know the rules, they all start to make sense.

00:43.858 --> 00:46.202
So today we learn the rules:

00:46.552 --> 00:51.629
atoms, elements, molecules, compounds, and mixtures.
